\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces Reliability diagrams of the twelve configurations, grouped by prompt variant (Prompt~A on the left, Prompt~B on the right), with each curve corresponding to one of the six models. Each curve plots the observed accuracy (labelled \emph  {Précision observée}) as a function of predicted confidence (\emph  {Confiance prédite}) in ten equal-width bins; the dashed reference line labelled \emph  {Parfait} corresponds to perfect calibration. Deviations from the diagonal $y = x$ indicate miscalibration; the direction of the deviation is consistent with the mean overconfidence reported in Table~\ref {tab:res-overconf}. Axis labels and the legend are kept in French, reflecting the working language of the experimental phase.}}{45}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
